wtWebGraphAnalog57661ValuesTable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661ValuesTable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661ValuesTable.description: List of measurement values corresponding to the channel numbers.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661Values.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661Values
wtWebGraphAnalog57661Values.description: Measurement value of the sensor, ASCII. This value will be translated according to the ports settings for the read and write operations.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryValuesTable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryValuesTable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryValuesTable.description: List of binary measurement values corresponding to the channel numbers.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryValuesEntry.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryValuesEntry
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryValuesEntry.description: Binary measurement values of the sensors.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryValues.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryValues
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryValues.description: Binary measurement value of the sensor in 1/1000, signed number, 0x7FFFFFFF indicates an invalid value. This value will be translated according to the ports settings for the read and write operations.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlPassword.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlPassword
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlPassword.description: Entering this password opens a session which is ended by writing a 1 to wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlLogout. When read this variable provides a string of length zero.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlConfigMode.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlConfigMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlConfigMode.description: When the device is in SNMP configuration mode, the value 1 is returned, otherwise 0. If the read value is 0 even though the password was written, the device is already in config mode and the variables can only be read.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlLogout.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlLogout
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlLogout.description: If the device is in configuration mode and the session was opened by this SNMP Manager, writing a 1 to this variable will end the session and all parameters are stored. Writing a 2 discards all entries again. When read this variable provides the value 0.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlAdminPassw.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlAdminPassword
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlAdminPassw.description: This password protects access to the variables with administrator rights. It can only be changed by the administrator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlConfigPass.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlConfigPassword
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SessCntrlConfigPass.description: This password protects access to the variables with configurator rights. It can be changed by the administrator and by the configurator. If no password was assigned, the valid password is public. When read this variable provides a null-pointer.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceName.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceName
wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceName.description: Name of the Webio, which is user definable.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceText.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceText
wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceText.description: Description of the Webio, which is user definable.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceLocation.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceLocation
wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceLocation.description: Description of the location of the Webio, which is user definable.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceContact.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceContact
wtWebGraphAnalog57661DeviceContact.description: Contact address of the system operator of the Webio, which is user definable.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661TzOffsetHrs.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661TzOffsetHrs
wtWebGraphAnalog57661TzOffsetHrs.description: Offset hours for the time zone (winter time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661TzOffsetMin.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661TzOffsetMin
wtWebGraphAnalog57661TzOffsetMin.description: Offset minutes for the time zone (winter time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661TzEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661TzEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661TzEnable.description: Binary coded conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Apply Timezone

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzOffsetHrs.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzOffsetHrs
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzOffsetHrs.description: Offset hours of the time zone (summer time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzOffsetMin.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzOffsetMin
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzOffsetMin.description: Offset minutes of the time zone (summer time) with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzEnable.description: Binary coded conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Apply Summertime

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartMonth.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartMonth
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartMonth.description: Month in which the change is made from winter time to summer time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartMode.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartMode.description: Mode of the day of the week for which the change is made from winter time to summer time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartWday.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartWday
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartWday.description: Day of the week on which the change is made from winter time to summer time

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartHrs.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartHrs
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartHrs.description: Hour in which the time zone is changed from winter to summer time with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartMin.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartMin
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStartMin.description: Minute in which the time zone is changed from winter to summer time with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopMonth.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopMonth
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopMonth.description: Month in which the change is made from summer time to winter time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopMode.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopMode.description: Mode of the week day on which the change is made from summer time to winter time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopWday.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopWday
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopWday.description: Day of the week on which the change is made from summer time to winter time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopHrs.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopHrs
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopHrs.description: Hour at which the time zone is changed from summer to winter time with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopMin.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopMin
wtWebGraphAnalog57661StTzStopMin.description: Minute at which the time zone is changed from summer to winter time with respect to UTC.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661TimeServer1.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661TimeServer1
wtWebGraphAnalog57661TimeServer1.description: IP address or name of the 1st time server in ASCII

wtWebGraphAnalog57661TimeServer2.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661TimeServer2
wtWebGraphAnalog57661TimeServer2.description: IP address or name of the 2nd time server in ASCII

wtWebGraphAnalog57661TsEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661TsEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661TsEnable.description: Binary coded conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Apply Time Server

wtWebGraphAnalog57661TsSyncTime.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661TsSyncTime
wtWebGraphAnalog57661TsSyncTime.description: Daily synchronisation time with the time server (hour: 0-23).

wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockHrs.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockHrs
wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockHrs.description: Clock hours taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockMin.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockMin
wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockMin.description: Clock minutes taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockDay.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockDay
wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockDay.description: Date: Day of the month, taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockMonth.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockMonth
wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockMonth.description: Date: Month, taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockYear.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockYear
wtWebGraphAnalog57661ClockYear.description: Date: Year, taking into account the time zone settings.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661DnsServer1.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661DnsServer1
wtWebGraphAnalog57661DnsServer1.description: IP address of the 1st DNS server in ASCII

wtWebGraphAnalog57661DnsServer2.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661DnsServer2
wtWebGraphAnalog57661DnsServer2.description: IP address of the 2nd DNS server in ASCII

wtWebGraphAnalog57661AddConfig.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661AddConfig
wtWebGraphAnalog57661AddConfig.description: Additional configuration (1=ON): Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1: DHCP disable Bit 0: BOOTP disable

wtWebGraphAnalog57661Startup.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661Startup
wtWebGraphAnalog57661Startup.description: Binary coded start page: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1: Index.htm Bit 2: Home.htm Bit 3: User.htm Only one page may be selected at a time.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661GetHeaderEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661GetHeaderEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661GetHeaderEnable.description: If these bits are set, every answer of a short form GET question will be lead by the IP-address and name of the device and/or a HTTP header: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-6: unused Bit 1 : GET HTTP enable Bit 0 : GET Header enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57661HttpPort.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661HttpPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661HttpPort.description: Definition of the standard HTML port (Default: 80).

wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailReply.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailReply
wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailReply.description: Reply address for the mail server.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailServer.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailServer
wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailServer.description: Name or IP address of the mail server.

wtWebioAn1MailEnable.name: wtWebioAn1MailEnable
wtWebioAn1MailEnable.description: Set this bit to enable the sending of mails: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Mail enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailAuthentication.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailAuthentication
wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailAuthentication.description: Selection of the authentication modi: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : POP3 before SMTP Bit 1 : ESMTP, authentication Bit 0 : SMTP, no authentication

wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailAuthUser.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailAuthUser
wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailAuthUser.description: Name of the user to be authenticated.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailPop3Server.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailPop3Server
wtWebGraphAnalog57661MailPop3Server.description: Name or Ip-address of the POP3 Servers.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SystemTrapManagerIP.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SystemTrapManagerIP
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SystemTrapManagerIP.description: Name or IP address of the TCP server which accepts the system trap.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SystemTrapEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SystemTrapEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SystemTrapEnable.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: ColdStart Bit 1: WarmStart Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SnmpEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SnmpEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SnmpEnable.description: Set bit 0 to enable SNMP. If disabled, the device did not respond to any SNMP requests. Bit 1 decided wether the community string of read operations is compared with the system password or not: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : SNMP enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57661UdpPort.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661UdpPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661UdpPort.description: Udp port to which the Udp queries ( short form GET requests) can be sent. This port number must be unique within the device.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661UdpEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661UdpEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661UdpEnable.description: Set this bit to enable UDP support: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : UDP enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogServerIP.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogServerIP
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the Syslog server, which accepts the Syslog messgaes.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogServerPort.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogServerPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogServerPort.description: Portnumber of the Syslog servers, default 514.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogSystemMessage.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogSystemMessagesEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogSystemMessage.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: ColdStart Bit 1: WarmStart Bit 2: Diag Messages Bit 3-7: unused

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SyslogEnable.description: Set bit 0to enable Syslog: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Syslog enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPServerIP.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPServerIP
wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPServerIP.description: Name or IP address of the FTP server, which accepts the FTP messages.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPServerControlPor.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPServerControlPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPServerControlPor.description: Portnumber of the control port of the FTP server, default 21.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPOption.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPOption
wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPOption.description: Bit 0 switches the FTP Server in Passiv-Mode, the Client controls the data connection on its own: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : PASV enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661FTPEnable.description: Set Bit 0 to enable FTP: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : FTP enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57661LanguageSelect.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661LanguageSelect
wtWebGraphAnalog57661LanguageSelect.description: Language selection: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 2-7: unused Bit 1 : English Bit 0 : German

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTable.description: Table of properties of the binary mode.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryOperationMode.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryOperationMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryOperationMode.description: Selection of the operation mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : UDP Peer Bit 1 : TCP Client Bit 0 : TCP Server

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerLoca.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerLocalPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerLoca.description: Local TCP port for data exchange in this server mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerInpu.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerInputTrigger
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerInpu.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input states. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Analog inputs 0-1

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerAppl.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerApplicationMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerAppl.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 4-7: unused Bit 3 : OPC Device Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientLoca.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientLocalPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientLoca.description: Local TCP port for data exchange in this client mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServ.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServerPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServ.description: Port number of the server. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the server port to zero.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServ.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServerIpAddr
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServ.description: Ip address of the server. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the server IP address to 0.0.0.0.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServ.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServerPassword
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServ.description: Building a connection may be protected by the administrator password of the server. Enter the server password to establish the connection, if a server administrator password exists.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientInac.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientInactivity
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientInac.description: Connection timeout in 100ms. If no data are exchanged within the specified time, the device closes the connection to the server. The value 0 deactivates the timer. Using the Box2Box mode this function is disabled.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientInpu.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientInputTrigger
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientInpu.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input states. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Analog inputs 0-1

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientInte.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientInterval
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientInte.description: Configurable interval with a 100ms base, in which the Webio device sends data to the configured application. A interval of zero stopps the periodical sending.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientAppl.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientApplicationMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientAppl.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerLocalP.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerLocalPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerLocalP.description: Local UDP port for data exchange in this peer to peer mode. This port number must be unique within the device. Reserved port number must not be used (refere to the manual).

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerRemote.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerRemotePort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerRemote.description: Port number of the remote device. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the remote port to zero.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerRemote.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerRemoteIpAddr
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerRemote.description: Ip address of the remote device. A complete set of port number, IP address and a valid input/output mask starts this mode. No data exchange take place when setting the remote device IP address to 0.0.0.0.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerInputT.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerInputTrigger
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerInputT.description: Every change on the inputs causes their state to be transmitted to the remote device. To minimize data traffic, individual inputs may be exempted from this rule. Nevertheless every transmission will contain all input states. If a bit is set (1), a change of state on the corresponding input triggers a transmission. If the bit is not set (0), no transmission takes place. The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an input. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4, Bit 0-1: Analog inputs 0-1

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerInterv.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerInterval
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerInterv.description: Configurable interval with a 100ms base, in which the Webio device sends data to the configured remote device. A interval of zero stopps the periodical sending.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerApplic.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerApplicationMode
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerApplic.description: Selection of the application mode: The OCTETS are interpreted bit-by-bit, with each bit corresponding to an output. Bit 0 corresponds to the LSB. OCTET 1: unused OCTET 2: unused OCTET 3: unused OCTET 4: Bit 3-7: unused Bit 2 : Box2Box Slave Bit 1 : Compatible 50xxx Bit 0 : Default

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryConnectedPort.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryConnectedPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryConnectedPort.description: Port number of the remote device, after connection has been established. In case of no connection or missing port informations a zero will be read.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryConnectedIpAd.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryConnectedIpAddr
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryConnectedIpAd.description: IP address of the remote device, after connection has been established. In case of no connection or missing port informations 0.0.0.0 will be read.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerClie.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerClientHttpPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerClie.description: HTTP port number of the remote device at TCP Server Mode. If an mailfunction occurs status informations will be send to this port. Not used at mode Compatible 50xxx.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServ.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServerHttpPort
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientServ.description: HTTP port number of the remote device at TCP Client Mode. In the operating mode Box2Box connection status informations will be exchanged through this port.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerHyst.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerHysteresis1
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerHyst.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 1 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerHyst.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerHysteresis2
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerHyst.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 2 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpServerInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientHyst.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientHysteresis1
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientHyst.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 1 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientHyst.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientHysteresis2
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientHyst.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 2 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryTcpClientInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerHyster.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerHysteresis1
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerHyster.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 1 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerHyster.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerHysteresis2
wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerHyster.description: A change greater than this value initiate a transmission of the corresponding input value. The input 2 must be selected at wtWebGraphAnalog57661BinaryUdpPeerInputTrigger. With a hysteresis of zero any change will be transmitted.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661LoggerTimebase.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661LoggerTimebase
wtWebGraphAnalog57661LoggerTimebase.description: Time base of the data logger

wtWebGraphAnalog57661LoggerSensorSel.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661LoggerSensorSel
wtWebGraphAnalog57661LoggerSensorSel.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: Sensor 1 Bit 1: Sensor 2 Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebGraphAnalog57661DisplaySensorSel.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661DisplaySensorSel
wtWebGraphAnalog57661DisplaySensorSel.description: Binary coded sensor selection: only selected sensors will be shown in the graphical presentation: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 0: Sensor 1 Bit 1: Sensor 2 Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SensorColorTable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SensorColorTable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SensorColorTable.description: List of sensor colors for the praphical presentation.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661SensorColor.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661SensorColor
wtWebGraphAnalog57661SensorColor.description: Color of the sensors at the praphical presention.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661AutoScaleEnable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661AutoScaleEnable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661AutoScaleEnable.description: If bit 0 is set, vertical auto scale is enabled: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: unused Octet 4: Bit 1-7: unused Bit 0 : Auto Scale enable

wtWebGraphAnalog57661VerticalUpperLimit.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661VerticalUpperLimit
wtWebGraphAnalog57661VerticalUpperLimit.description: This value defines the maximum temperature shown in the graphical presentation, if no auto scaling is selected. Temperature in degrees with maximum 2 decimal places.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661VerticalLowerLimit.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661VerticalLowerLimit
wtWebGraphAnalog57661VerticalLowerLimit.description: This value defines the minimum temperature shown in the graphical presentation, if no auto scaling is selected. Temperature in degrees with maximum 2 decimal places.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661HorizontalZoom.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661HorizontalZoom
wtWebGraphAnalog57661HorizontalZoom.description: Defines the default zoom stage, if no auto scaling is selected.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmTable.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmTable
wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmTable.description: List of settings depending on the alarm number.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmEntry.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmEntry
wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmEntry.description: Alarm parameters of the individual alarms.

wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmTrigger.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmTrigger
wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmTrigger.description: Binary coded trigger conditions: Octet 1: unused Octet 2: unused Octet 3: Bit 0: Timer Bit 1: ColdStart Bit 2: WarmStart Octet 4: Bit 0: Sensor 1 Bit 1: Sensor 2 Bit 2-7: unused

wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmMin1.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmMin1

wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmTimerCron.name: wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmTimerCron
wtWebGraphAnalog57661AlarmTimerCron.description: This entry defines a time window for alarm 1-8 and a activation time for the report. A time window is definied by start and stop time stamp, seperated by a space or tab. The activation time of the report is defined by a single start time stamp. Each time stamp contains 5 space or tab seperated text fields for time trigger definition. Each field must match with the actual time to trigger an action, weekday and day of month are interpreted separatley. 1: Minutes Range 0-59 2. Hours Range 0-23, 0 is midnight 3: Day of month Range 1-31 4: Month Range 1-12 5: Weekday Range 0-6, 0 is sunday Syntax for every field: - an asterix (*) enables every possible setting of a field - single numbers seperated by commas (i.e.: 2,14,22) - a partition within the allowed range (i.e.: 1-5) - step size within a partition of the allowed range (i.e.: 0-59/2 every second minute).
